com.ibm.collaboration.realtime.gateway.plugin
Interface PluginPresenceHandler

All Superinterfaces:
PluginRegistration
public interface PluginPresenceHandler
extends PluginRegistration

This interface may be implemented by message handler plug-ins to receive notifications on presence awareness requests passing through the gateway.

Since:
7.5

Method Detail

fetch

void fetch(PresenceEvent event,
           boolean isNewSession)
This method is called by the originating user to quickly retrieve the status of the destination user. In many cases this is performed during resubscribe operation to check the user status after a time-out occurs with the initial subscribe request.

Parameters:
event - - the presence event status
isNewSession - - true if this is a new fetch request. False if this method is called during resubscribe request

notify

void notify(PresenceEvent notifyEvent)
This method is called when the notify message is sent to the subscriber to inform the change of the user status. Notify message is sent to the message handler plugins that registered on this event.

Parameters:
notifyEvent - - the notify event sent to the plugin

onFetch

void onFetch(EventStatus status,
             boolean isNewSession)
This method is called when the destination community has processed the fetch request for user status update.

Parameters:
event - - the status of the fetch event
isNewSession - - true if this is a new fetch request. False if the fetch request is called during resubscribe request.

onNotify

void onNotify(EventStatus notifyEvent)
This method is called when the originating community has processed the Notify request.

Parameters:
notifyEvent - - the notification event status

onSubscribe

void onSubscribe(EventStatus subEvent)
This method is called when the destination community has processed the request from the originating user to receive notifications.

Parameters:
subEvent - - the subscription event status

onUnsubscribe

void onUnsubscribe(EventStatus subEvent)
This method is called when the destination community has processed the request from the originating user to receive notifications.

Parameters:
subEvent - - the subscription event status

subscribe

void subscribe(PresenceEvent subEvent)
This method is called when the originating user informs to the destination community to notify the status of the destination user.

Parameters:
subEvent - - PresenceEvent

unsubscribe

void unsubscribe(PresenceEvent unsubEvent)
This method is called when the originating user no longer wishes to receive notifications of the status of the destination user.

Parameters:
unsubEvent - - the presence event sent to the plugin
